# GCP iam-tunnel — VM self-heal & remote git

**Load when:** `FETCH_HEAD` permission denied, `git@github.com: Permission denied (publickey)`, ExecOS sync failures, terminal.inneranimalmedia.com down, or post-deploy GCP VM issues.

## Architecture (do not confuse users)

| Layer | User | Role |
|-------|------|------|
| Mac operator | `samprimeaux` | `gh` + `GITHUB_TOKEN` in `.env.cloudflare`; deploy from Mac |
| VM login | `samprimeaux` | gcloud SSH target; has GitHub SSH + gh |
| VM runtime | **`agentsam`** | Owns `~/inneranimalmedia/.git`, `~/ExecOS/.git`, **pm2 execos** |

**Git on VM uses SSH keys, not `GITHUB_TOKEN`.** Token powers `gh` for `samprimeaux` only. Repo `.git` is owned by `agentsam` — `git pull` as `samprimeaux` → `FETCH_HEAD: Permission denied`.

**pm2 execos runs as `agentsam`** (`PM2_HOME=/var/lib/agentsam/.pm2`). Never restart execos via `samprimeaux` pm2 (empty list).

## deploy:full vs VM

### BANNED on iam-tunnel (LOCKED)

Never run on the GCP VM:

- `npm run deploy:full`
- `npm run deploy:fast` / Vite / `npm --prefix dashboard run build`
- rclone dashboard sync

Ship from the VM with: **`npm run ship:remote`** (push → Cloudflare Builds).  
SSOT: `docs/platform/mac-free-ship-lanes-2026-07.md` · `.cursor/rules/iam-ship-lanes.mdc`

### Post-deploy VM sync (Mac ran deploy)

- Default: **`IAM_SYNC_GCP_EXECOS=0`** — deploy does **not** SCP or force ExecOS sync.
- VM self-heals every 5 min via root cron.
- Opt-in force sync: `IAM_SYNC_GCP_EXECOS=1 npm run deploy:full` (Mac only)
- Skip all VM sync: `IAM_SKIP_GCP_VM_SYNC=1`

## Common errors → fix

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
|---------|-------|-----|
| `cannot open '.git/FETCH_HEAD': Permission denied` | Pull as wrong user | Pull as `agentsam` (see below) |
| `Permission denied (publickey)` as `agentsam` | No SSH in `/var/lib/agentsam/.ssh` | Run setup script (below) |
| pm2 execos "not running" but terminal OK | Checked `samprimeaux` pm2 | `sudo -u agentsam pm2 list` |
| ExecOS ff-only pull fails | VM branch diverged | `git fetch && git reset --hard origin/main` as `agentsam` |

## One-shot fix from Mac (preferred)

```bash
# From repo root — needs gcloud + .env.cloudflare GCP_PROJECT_ID/GCP_ZONE
./scripts/setup-gcp-vm-self-heal-once.sh
```

This: mirrors Sam SSH key → `agentsam`, git pull both repos, installs root cron, runs self-heal once.

If `samprimeaux` lost gh/SSH on VM first:

```bash
./scripts/install-terminal-github-cli.sh --gcp-only --prompt-token
./scripts/setup-gcp-vm-self-heal-once.sh
```

## Manual diagnose on VM (gcloud SSH)

```bash
export PATH="/opt/homebrew/bin:$PATH"
source .env.cloudflare
gcloud compute ssh iam-tunnel --project="$GCP_PROJECT_ID" --zone="$GCP_ZONE" --tunnel-through-iap
```

On VM:

```bash
# Who can reach GitHub?
ssh -T git@github.com                                    # samprimeaux
sudo -u agentsam ssh -T git@github.com                     # agentsam — must succeed

# Repo ownership
ls -la ~/inneranimalmedia/.git/FETCH_HEAD                # expect agentsam:agentsam

# Git pull (correct user)
sudo -u agentsam git -C ~/inneranimalmedia pull --ff-only
sudo -u agentsam git -C ~/ExecOS pull --ff-only

# pm2 + health
sudo -u agentsam pm2 list
curl -sf https://terminal.inneranimalmedia.com/health
sudo crontab -l | grep -E 'self-heal|health-watchdog'
tail -30 /var/log/iam-self-heal.log
```

